- teacher-only getExerciseAnalytics aggregates all attempts for a
  guide: unique students, total attempts, pass rate by best attempt,
  average best score, and per-question correct rates (recomputed
  against the current answer key via the shared gradeTask)
- analytics panel renders below the editor for auto-graded guides,
  questions sorted hardest-first with color-coded correct rates and
  goal tags — a low rate flags either a hard concept or a confusing
  question, both worth teacher attention
- pure aggregation lives in computeExerciseAnalytics (unit-tested);
  the action is a thin teacher-gated wrapper
---
